 🚀 ZIP Extractor PRO

A powerful and user-friendly **Python GUI tool** to recursively extract ZIP files, organize them automatically, and optionally delete ZIP files after extraction.

---
✨ Features

* 📂 Recursively scans folders and subfolders
* 📦 Extracts all ZIP files automatically
* 📁 Creates organized folders (same name as ZIP)
* 🗑 Option to delete ZIP files after extraction
* ⚡ Fast and smooth (non-blocking UI using threading)
* 📊 Real-time progress bar and statistics
* 📝 Live logs with status updates
* 🎨 Clean and modern dark UI

---

 🖥️ Preview

* Select input folder
* Optional output folder
* Enable delete option
* Click **Start 🚀**
* Watch progress + logs in real-time

---

 📦 Installation

 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/zip-extractor-pro.git
cd zip-extractor-pro
```

### 2. Install requirements

No external libraries required ✅
(Uses built-in Python modules)

---

 ▶️ Usage

Run the application:

```bash
python unzip_gui.py
```

---

⚙️ How It Works

1. Select a main folder
2. The app scans for all `.zip` files
3. Each ZIP is extracted into a folder with the same name
4. Progress is displayed in real-time
5. Optionally deletes ZIP files after extraction

---

 📊 Output Example

### Before:

```
D:\SOFTCORE PART-B\
 ├── folder1\
 │    ├── data.zip
```

After:

```
D:\SOFTCORE PART-B\
 ├── folder1\
 │    ├── data\
 │         ├── extracted files...
```

---

 📈 Stats Summary

After completion, you will see:

* Total ZIP files
* Extracted files
* Skipped files
* Failed files
* Deleted ZIPs

---

## ⚠️ Important Notes

* ❗ Close ZIP files before running
* ❗ Use **Delete option carefully** (files are permanently removed)
* ❗ Run as administrator if facing permission issues

---
 🛠 Tech Stack

* Python 🐍
* Tkinter (GUI)
* Threading (Performance)
* Zipfile (Extraction)

